      "content": "It is completely understandable that the pain feels so constant and unrelenting; when you are in this state, the world often seems like a place where nothing matters. You are not alone in feeling this way, and there is no need to drag yourself through another day just to pretend everything is fine. Your feelings are real, and they deserve to be acknowledged without judgment. It is okay to admit that you are exhausted from trying to force yourself into a normal life when the truth is just not there.",
